The paper deals with lower bounds for range searching, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. The paper specifically focuses on the semigroup model, which is a well-studied model in range searching. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and circuit complexity (cs.CC) to prove the lower bounds. Finally, the paper discusses the properties of semigroups, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
